trans-unit.source: The type of the elements contained in the queue.
trans-unit.target: O tipo dos elementos contidos na fila.

trans-unit.source: Represents a thread-safe first in-first out (FIFO) collection.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma coleção thread-safe PEPS (primeiro a entrar, primeiro a sair).

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> implements the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyCollection%601> interface starting with the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](~/includes/net-v46-md.md)]; in previous versions of the .NET Framework, the <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> class did not implement this interface.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> implementa o <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyCollection%601> interface começando com o [!INCLUDE[net_v46](~/includes/net-v46-md.md)]; nas versões anteriores do .NET Framework, o <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> classe não implementou esta interface.

trans-unit.target: Todos os membros protegidos e públicos da <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> são thread-safe e podem ser usados simultaneamente em vários threads.

trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that iterates through the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" />.
trans-unit.target: Retorna um enumerador que itera por meio de <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" />.

trans-unit.source: An enumerator for the contents of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" />.
trans-unit.target: Um enumerador para o conteúdo de <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" />.

trans-unit.source: The enumeration represents a moment-in-time snapshot of the contents of the queue.
trans-unit.target: A enumeração representa um instantâneo do momento-in-time do conteúdo da fila.

trans-unit.source: It does not reflect any updates to the collection after <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.GetEnumerator%2A> was called.
trans-unit.target: Ele não reflete todas as atualizações para a coleção após <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.GetEnumerator%2A> foi chamado.

trans-unit.source: The enumerator is safe to use concurrently with reads from and writes to the queue.
trans-unit.target: O enumerador é seguro usar simultaneamente com leituras de e grava na fila.

trans-unit.source: The enumerator returns the collection elements in the order in which they were added, which is FIFO order (first-in, first-out).
trans-unit.target: O enumerador retorna os elementos da coleção na ordem em que eles foram adicionados, que é a ordem FIFO (primeiro a entrar, primeiro a sair).

trans-unit.source: Gets a value that indicates whether the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> is empty.
trans-unit.target: Obtém um valor que indica se a <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> está vazia.

trans-unit.source: true if the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> is empty; otherwise, false.
trans-unit.target: true se a <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> estiver vazia, caso contrário, false.

trans-unit.source: For determining whether the collection contains any items, use of this property is recommended rather than retrieving the number of items from the <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.Count%2A> property and comparing it to 0.
trans-unit.target: Para determinar se a coleção contém todos os itens, é recomendável usar essa propriedade em vez de recuperar o número de itens a partir de <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.Count%2A> propriedade e compare-o como 0.

trans-unit.source: However, as this collection is intended to be accessed concurrently, it may be the case that another thread will modify the collection after <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.IsEmpty%2A> returns, thus invalidating the result.
trans-unit.target: No entanto, como essa coleção se destina a ser acessadas simultaneamente, ele pode ser o caso que outro thread irá modificar a coleção após <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.IsEmpty%2A> retorna, portanto, invalidando o resultados.

trans-unit.target: true se um elemento tiver sido removido e tiver retornado com êxito; caso contrário, false.

trans-unit.target: Quando este método retornar, se a operação tiver sido bem-sucedida, <c>result</c> conterá o objeto removido.

trans-unit.target: Caso nenhum objeto esteja disponível para ser removido, o valor é não especificado.

trans-unit.source: Tries to remove and return the object at the beginning of the concurrent queue.
trans-unit.target: Tenta remover e retornar o objeto no início da fila simultânea.

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if an element was removed and returned from the beginning of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> successfully; otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
trans-unit.target: <see langword="true" /> se um elemento tiver sido removido e retornado do início do <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> com êxito; caso contrário, <see langword="false" />.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> handles all synchronization internally.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> manipula todas as sincronizações internamente.

trans-unit.source: If two threads call <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.TryDequeue%2A> at precisely the same moment, neither operation is blocked.
trans-unit.target: Se dois threads chamada <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.TryDequeue%2A> exatamente no mesmo momento, nenhuma operação está bloqueada.

trans-unit.source: When a conflict is detected between two threads, one thread has to try again to retrieve the next element, and the synchronization is handled internally.
trans-unit.target: Quando é detectado um conflito entre dois threads, tem um thread tentar novamente recuperar o próximo elemento e a sincronização é manipulada internamente.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.TryDequeue%2A> tries to remove an element from the queue.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.TryDequeue%2A> tenta remover um elemento da fila.

trans-unit.source: If the method is successful, the item is removed and the method returns `true`; otherwise, it returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Se o método for bem-sucedida, o item é removido e o método retornará `true`; caso contrário, retornará `false`.

trans-unit.source: That happens atomically with respect to other operations on the queue.
trans-unit.target: Isso acontece atomicamente em relação a outras operações na fila.

trans-unit.source: If the queue was populated with code such as `q.Enqueue("a"); q.Enqueue("b"); q.Enqueue("c");` and two threads concurrently try to dequeue an element, one thread will dequeue `a` and the other thread will dequeue `b`.
trans-unit.target: Se a fila foi preenchida com o código como `q.Enqueue("a"); q.Enqueue("b"); q.Enqueue("c");` e dois threads simultaneamente tentarem um elemento de remoção da fila, um thread retirará `a` e o outro segmento retirará `b`.

trans-unit.source: Both calls to <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.TryDequeue%2A> will return `true`, because they were both able to dequeue an element.
trans-unit.target: As duas chamadas para <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601.TryDequeue%2A> retornará `true`, porque eles foram ambas capaz de um elemento de remoção da fila.

trans-unit.source: If each thread goes back to dequeue an additional element, one of the threads will dequeue `c` and return `true`, whereas the other thread will find the queue empty and will return `false`.
trans-unit.target: Se cada thread de volta para um elemento adicional de remoção da fila, um dos threads dequeue `c` e retornar `true`, enquanto o outro segmento localizar a fila vazia e retornará `false`.

trans-unit.source: When this method returns, <c>result</c> contains an object from the beginning of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> or an unspecified value if the operation failed.
trans-unit.target: Quando este método retorna, <c>result</c> contém um objeto do início do <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> ou um valor não especificado quando a operação falha.

trans-unit.source: Tries to return an object from the beginning of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> without removing it.
trans-unit.target: Tenta retornar um objeto do início da <see cref="T:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue`1" /> sem removê-lo.

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if an object was returned successfully; otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
trans-unit.target: <see langword="true" /> se um objeto foi retornado com sucesso, caso contrário, <see langword="false" />.
